  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्यव्रतेन पुरुषः धर्ममार्गे स्थितः।",
    "transliteration": "satya-vratena puruṣaḥ dharmamārge sthitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "By following truth and vows, one remains steadfast on the path of righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "सदाचारैः पुण्येनैव पुरुषः शुद्धिं प्राप्नोति।",
    "transliteration": "sadācāraiḥ puṇyenaiva puruṣaḥ śuddhiṃ prāpnoti ||",
    "translation_english": "Through virtuous conduct and merit, a person attains purity."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "योगसाधकः सत्यज्ञानं धारयेत् मोक्षमार्गे स्थिरः।",
    "transliteration": "yoga-sādhakaḥ satya-jñānaṃ dhārayed mokṣamārge sthiraḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "A practitioner of yoga holding true knowledge remains steadfast on the path of liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "सदाचारैः पूज्यते जीवः ब्रह्मसिद्धिं प्राप्नोति।",
    "transliteration": "sadācāraiḥ pūjyate jīvaḥ brahma-siddhiṃ prāpnoti ||",
    "translation_english": "By virtuous conduct, the soul is honored and attains perfection in Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "ध्यानयोगेन साधकः ब्रह्मसन्निधानं प्राप्नोति।",
    "transliteration": "dhyānayogena sādhakaḥ brahma-sannidhānaṃ prāpnoti ||",
    "translation_english": "Through meditation, the practitioner attains the presence of Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्यज्ञानं धारयेत् पुरुषः मोक्षमार्गे स्थिरः।",
    "transliteration": "satya-jñānaṃ dhārayed puruṣaḥ mokṣamārge sthiraḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "A person holding firm to true knowledge remains steadfast on the path of liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "सदाचारैः पुण्येन पुरुषः शुद्धिं प्राप्नोति।",
    "transliteration": "sadācāraiḥ puṇyena puruṣaḥ śuddhiṃ prāpnoti ||",
    "translation_english": "Through virtuous deeds, a person attains purity."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 7,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं सप्तमः अध्यायः समाप्तः।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ saptamaḥ adhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the seventh chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },


  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "ऋषय ऊचुः— भगवन् धर्मतत्त्वं नः विस्तार्य कथय प्रभो।",
    "transliteration": "ṛṣaya ūcuḥ — bhagavan dharmatattvaṃ naḥ vistārya kathaya prabho ||",
    "translation_english": "The sages said: O Lord, kindly explain to us in detail the true nature of righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "येन मार्गेण गच्छन्ति नराः स्वर्गं परां गतिम्।",
    "transliteration": "yena mārgeṇa gacchanti narāḥ svargaṃ parāṃ gatim ||",
    "translation_english": "Which path should humans follow to attain heaven and the supreme goal?"
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "ब्रह्मोवाच— धर्मः सत्यं तपो दानं शौचं क्षान्तिरहिंसा।",
    "transliteration": "brahmovāca — dharmaḥ satyaṃ tapo dānaṃ śaucaṃ kṣāntirahiṃsā ||",
    "translation_english": "Brahmā said: Righteousness consists of truth, austerity, charity, purity, patience, and non-violence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "एतेषु स्थितचित्तानां मोक्षो भवति निश्चितः।",
    "transliteration": "eteṣu sthitacittānāṃ mokṣo bhavati niścitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "For those firmly established in these virtues, liberation is assured."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "यज्ञदानतपोयुक्तः पुरुषः स्वर्गमश्नुते।",
    "transliteration": "yajña-dāna-tapo-yuktaḥ puruṣaḥ svargam aśnute ||",
    "translation_english": "A person devoted to sacrifice, charity, and austerity attains heaven."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "नित्यं धर्मे स्थितो यस्तु स याति ब्रह्मणः पदम्।",
    "transliteration": "nityaṃ dharme sthito yastu sa yāti brahmaṇaḥ padam ||",
    "translation_english": "One who constantly abides in righteousness attains the abode of Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "अहिंसा परमो धर्मः सर्वभूतेषु यः स्मृतः।",
    "transliteration": "ahiṃsā paramo dharmaḥ sarvabhūteṣu yaḥ smṛtaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Non-violence is declared the highest form of righteousness toward all beings."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "सन्तोषः परमं सौख्यं धर्मस्य मूलमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "santoṣaḥ paramaṃ saukhyaṃ dharmasya mūlam ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Contentment is the greatest happiness and is said to be the root of dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 9,
    "sanskrit_text": "यः परेषां प्रियं कुर्यात् स धर्मात्मा प्रकीर्तितः।",
    "transliteration": "yaḥ pareṣāṃ priyaṃ kuryāt sa dharmātmā prakīrtitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "He who acts for the welfare of others is called truly righteous."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 10,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण जीवितं येषां तेषां न भयमस्ति वै।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa jīvitaṃ yeṣāṃ teṣāṃ na bhayam asti vai ||",
    "translation_english": "Those who live by righteousness are free from fear."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 11,
    "sanskrit_text": "कर्मणा मनसा वाचा धर्म एव विधीयते।",
    "transliteration": "karmaṇā manasā vācā dharma eva vidhīyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Righteousness is practiced through action, thought, and speech."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 12,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं धर्मः समाख्यातो ब्रह्मलोकप्रदायकः।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ dharmaḥ samākhyāto brahmaloka-pradāyakaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus, righteousness has been explained as the giver of the world of Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "श्रद्धया यः पठेन्नित्यं स धर्मफलमश्नुते।",
    "transliteration": "śraddhayā yaḥ paṭhennityaṃ sa dharma-phalam aśnute ||",
    "translation_english": "One who regularly studies this with faith attains the fruits of righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "पुण्यं यशस्यमायुष्यं धर्मश्रवणजं फलम्।",
    "transliteration": "puṇyaṃ yaśasyam āyuṣyaṃ dharma-śravaṇajaṃ phalam ||",
    "translation_english": "Merit, fame, and long life arise from listening to teachings of dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मो रक्षति रक्षितः सर्वलोकहितावहः।",
    "transliteration": "dharmo rakṣati rakṣitaḥ sarvaloka-hitāvahaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Dharma protects those who protect it and brings welfare to all worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्ममूलं जगत्सर्वं स्थितं चराचरात्मकम्।",
    "transliteration": "dharmamūlaṃ jagat sarvaṃ sthitaṃ carācarātmakam ||",
    "translation_english": "The entire universe, moving and unmoving, is rooted in righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "तस्माद्धर्मः सदा सेव्यो मानवैः सुखकाम्यया।",
    "transliteration": "tasmād dharmaḥ sadā sevyo mānavaiḥ sukhakāmyayā ||",
    "translation_english": "Therefore, humans seeking happiness should always practice righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण लभते कीर्तिं धर्मेण लभते गतिम्।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa labhate kīrtiṃ dharmeṇa labhate gatim ||",
    "translation_english": "Through righteousness one gains fame, and through righteousness one attains liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण हीनः पुरुषः पशुभिः सम उच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa hīnaḥ puruṣaḥ paśubhiḥ sama ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "A person devoid of righteousness is said to be equal to an animal."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवमष्टम अध्यायः ब्रह्मपुराणे समाप्तः।",
    "transliteration": "evam aṣṭama adhyāyaḥ brahma-purāṇe samāptaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the eighth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },

  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 21,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मे स्थितस्य पुरुषस्य न कदाचिद् विनाशनम्।",
    "transliteration": "dharme sthitasya puruṣasya na kadācid vināśanam ||",
    "translation_english": "One who remains established in righteousness is never destroyed."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 22,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण जयते लोकान् धर्मेण जयते परम्।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa jayate lokān dharmeṇa jayate param ||",
    "translation_english": "Through righteousness one conquers the worlds, and through righteousness one attains the Supreme."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 23,
    "sanskrit_text": "न धर्मात् परमो लाभो न धर्मात् परमा गतिः।",
    "transliteration": "na dharmāt paramo lābho na dharmāt paramā gatiḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "There is no gain higher than righteousness, and no destination greater than righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 24,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण धार्यते लोकः सचराचर एव हि।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa dhāryate lokaḥ sacarācara eva hi ||",
    "translation_english": "Indeed, the entire world—moving and unmoving—is sustained by righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 25,
    "sanskrit_text": "राजानो धर्मरक्षार्थं पृथिवीं पालयन्ति हि।",
    "transliteration": "rājāno dharma-rakṣārthaṃ pṛthivīṃ pālayanti hi ||",
    "translation_english": "Kings rule the earth for the protection of righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 26,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्महीनं नृपं लोकाः क्षिप्रं त्यजन्ति दुःखिताः।",
    "transliteration": "dharmahīnaṃ nṛpaṃ lokāḥ kṣipraṃ tyajanti duḥkhitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "People quickly abandon a ruler devoid of righteousness, suffering under his rule."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 27,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मयुक्तो नृपो लोके कीर्तिं यश्चाधिगच्छति।",
    "transliteration": "dharmayukto nṛpo loke kīrtiṃ yaś cādhigacchati ||",
    "translation_english": "A righteous king attains fame and honor in the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 28,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्म एव गुरुः श्रेष्ठो धर्म एव पिता स्मृतः।",
    "transliteration": "dharma eva guruḥ śreṣṭho dharma eva pitā smṛtaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Righteousness itself is the greatest teacher and is regarded as one’s true father."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 29,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्म एव सखा लोके धर्म एव परायणम्।",
    "transliteration": "dharma eva sakhā loke dharma eva parāyaṇam ||",
    "translation_english": "Righteousness alone is one’s friend in the world and one’s ultimate refuge."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 30,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्ममाश्रित्य पुरुषः सर्वदुःखात् प्रमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "dharmam āśritya puruṣaḥ sarva-duḥkhāt pramucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "By taking refuge in righteousness, a person is freed from all suffering."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 31,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मो नारायणः साक्षात् सर्वलोकहिताय वै।",
    "transliteration": "dharmo nārāyaṇaḥ sākṣāt sarvaloka-hitāya vai ||",
    "translation_english": "Righteousness is verily Nārāyaṇa Himself, acting for the welfare of all worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 32,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मे स्थिताः प्रसीदन्ति देवा अपि न संशयः।",
    "transliteration": "dharme sthitāḥ prasīdanti devā api na saṃśayaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Even the gods are pleased with those established in righteousness—there is no doubt."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 33,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण तपसा चैव सर्वसिद्धिः प्रजायते।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa tapasā caiva sarva-siddhiḥ prajāyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Through righteousness and austerity, all accomplishments arise."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 34,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्ममूलं जगत्सर्वं धर्मे सर्वं प्रतिष्ठितम्।",
    "transliteration": "dharmamūlaṃ jagat sarvaṃ dharme sarvaṃ pratiṣṭhitam ||",
    "translation_english": "The entire universe is rooted in righteousness; everything stands upon it."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 35,
    "sanskrit_text": "य एवं वेत्ति धर्मस्य महत्त्वं स विमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "ya evaṃ vetti dharmasya mahatvaṃ sa vimucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "One who truly understands the greatness of righteousness attains liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 36,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मश्रवणमात्रेण पापराशिर्विनश्यति।",
    "transliteration": "dharma-śravaṇa-mātreṇa pāpa-rāśir vinaśyati ||",
    "translation_english": "By merely hearing about righteousness, heaps of sin are destroyed."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 37,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मोपदेशं श्रुत्वा मानवो भवति निर्मलः।",
    "transliteration": "dharmopadeśaṃ śrutvā mānavo bhavati nirmalaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Upon hearing teachings of righteousness, a person becomes pure."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 38,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण सह मोक्षश्च स्वर्गश्चैव प्रजायते।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa saha mokṣaś ca svargaś caiva prajāyate ||",
    "translation_english": "With righteousness come both liberation and heaven."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 39,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्म एव परं तत्त्वं ब्रह्मणा परिकीर्तितम्।",
    "transliteration": "dharma eva paraṃ tattvaṃ brahmaṇā parikīrtitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Righteousness alone is the supreme truth, as proclaimed by Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 40,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति धर्मोपदेशोऽयं ब्रह्मणा संप्रकीर्तितः।",
    "transliteration": "iti dharmopadeśo’yaṃ brahmaṇā samprakīrtitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends this teaching on righteousness as declared by Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 8,
    "verse": 41,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति ब्रह्मपुराणे अष्टमोऽध्यायः समाप्तः।",
    "transliteration": "iti brahma-purāṇe aṣṭamo’dhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the eighth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },


  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "ऋषय ऊचुः— सर्गं वंशान् मनूंश्चैव विस्तार्य कथय प्रभो।",
    "transliteration": "ṛṣaya ūcuḥ — sargaṃ vaṃśān manūṃś caiva vistārya kathaya prabho ||",
    "translation_english": "The sages said: O Lord, please explain in detail the creation, lineages, and the Manus."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "ब्रह्मोवाच— आदौ नारायणः सृष्टिं स्वेच्छया समकल्पयत्।",
    "transliteration": "brahmovāca — ādau nārāyaṇaḥ sṛṣṭiṃ svecchayā samakalpayat ||",
    "translation_english": "Brahmā said: In the beginning, Nārāyaṇa willed the creation by His own desire."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "अव्यक्तात् प्रथमे ब्रह्मा स्वयंभूः समजायत।",
    "transliteration": "avyaktāt prathame brahmā svayaṃbhūḥ samajāyata ||",
    "translation_english": "From the unmanifest arose Brahmā, the self-born creator."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "हिरण्यगर्भ इत्येष सृष्टिकर्ता प्रकीर्तितः।",
    "transliteration": "hiraṇyagarbha ityeṣa sṛṣṭikartā prakīrtitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "He is known as Hiraṇyagarbha, the creator of the universe."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "मनसा सृष्टिमादाय प्रजाः ससर्ज चात्मवान्।",
    "transliteration": "manasā sṛṣṭim ādāya prajāḥ sasarja cātmavān ||",
    "translation_english": "Using his mind, the self-possessed Brahmā created living beings."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "मरीच्यादीन् ऋषीन् पूर्वं मानसाः ससृजे प्रभुः।",
    "transliteration": "marīcyādīn ṛṣīn pūrvaṃ mānasāḥ sasarje prabhuḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "First, the Lord created the mind-born sages such as Marīci."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेभ्यः प्रजाः प्रसूयन्ते स्थावराः जङ्गमास्तथा।",
    "transliteration": "tebhyaḥ prajāḥ prasūyante sthāvarāḥ jaṅgamās tathā ||",
    "translation_english": "From them arose all beings—both immobile and mobile."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "मनवो धर्मकर्तारः सृष्टिरक्षणतत्पराः।",
    "transliteration": "manavo dharmakartāraḥ sṛṣṭirakṣaṇa-tatparāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The Manus became the lawgivers, devoted to preserving creation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 9,
    "sanskrit_text": "स्वायम्भुवो मनुः पूर्वं लोकस्य प्रभवो मतः।",
    "transliteration": "svāyambhuvo manuḥ pūrvaṃ lokasya prabhavo mataḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Svāyambhuva Manu is regarded as the first progenitor of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 10,
    "sanskrit_text": "तस्मादिक्ष्वाकुवंशश्च सूर्यवंशः प्रजायते।",
    "transliteration": "tasmād ikṣvāku-vaṃśaś ca sūryavaṃśaḥ prajāyate ||",
    "translation_english": "From him arose the Ikṣvāku lineage, the Solar dynasty."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 11,
    "sanskrit_text": "चन्द्रवंशश्च विप्रर्षे सोमादेव प्रजायते।",
    "transliteration": "candravaṃśaś ca viprarṣe somādeva prajāyate ||",
    "translation_english": "The Lunar dynasty arose from Soma, O sage."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 12,
    "sanskrit_text": "एते वंशा महात्मानः पृथिव्यां धर्मकारिणः।",
    "transliteration": "ete vaṃśā mahātmānaḥ pṛthivyāṃ dharmakāriṇaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "These great dynasties upheld righteousness upon the earth."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "सप्तद्वीपा वसुन्धरा सप्तसागरसंवृता।",
    "transliteration": "sapta-dvīpā vasundharā sapta-sāgara-saṃvṛtā ||",
    "translation_english": "The earth consists of seven continents surrounded by seven oceans."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "मेरुः पर्वतराजोऽत्र लोकानां मध्य उच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "meruḥ parvatarājo’tra lokānāṃ madhya ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Mount Meru, the king of mountains, stands at the center of the worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "लोकालोकः परो लोको यत्र सूर्यः न दृश्यते।",
    "transliteration": "lokālokaḥ paro loko yatra sūryaḥ na dṛśyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Beyond the known world lies Lokāloka, where the sun does not shine."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "कालः सृष्टिं लयं चैव नियच्छति न संशयः।",
    "transliteration": "kālaḥ sṛṣṭiṃ layaṃ caiva niyacchati na saṃśayaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Time governs both creation and dissolution without doubt."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "कल्पान्ते सर्वभूतानि विष्णौ लीयन्ति शाश्वते।",
    "transliteration": "kalpānte sarva-bhūtāni viṣṇau līyanti śāśvate ||",
    "translation_english": "At the end of a cosmic age, all beings dissolve into eternal Viṣṇu."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "एष सर्गः समाख्यातो यथावद् ऋषिसत्तमाः।",
    "transliteration": "eṣa sargaḥ samākhyāto yathāvad ṛṣi-sattamāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the process of creation has been properly explained, O great sages."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "य एतत् शृणुयान्नित्यं स ज्ञानं लभते परम्।",
    "transliteration": "ya etat śṛṇuyān nityaṃ sa jñānaṃ labhate param ||",
    "translation_english": "One who regularly hears this attains supreme knowledge."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "सृष्टिकथां समालोच्य पापैः स मुच्यते नरः।",
    "transliteration": "sṛṣṭi-kathāṃ samālocya pāpaiḥ sa mucyate naraḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "By contemplating the account of creation, a person is freed from sins."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 21,
    "sanskrit_text": "भूर् भुवः स्वः इति ख्याता लोकास्त्रय उदाहृताः।",
    "transliteration": "bhūr bhuvaḥ svaḥ iti khyātā lokās traya udāhṛtāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The three worlds are known as Bhūr, Bhuvaḥ, and Svaḥ."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 22,
    "sanskrit_text": "महर्जनस्तपः सत्यं क्रमशः परिकीर्तितम्।",
    "transliteration": "mahar janas tapaḥ satyaṃ kramaśaḥ parikīrtitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Above them are the realms of Mahar, Jana, Tapa, and Satya."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 23,
    "sanskrit_text": "एषां मध्ये स्थितो मेरुः प्रकाशो लोकदीपकः।",
    "transliteration": "eṣāṃ madhye sthito meruḥ prakāśo loka-dīpakaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Among these worlds stands Mount Meru, illuminating all realms."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 24,
    "sanskrit_text": "देवाः मेरुं समाश्रित्य निवसन्ति सहर्षिभिः।",
    "transliteration": "devāḥ meruṃ samāśritya nivasanti saha ṛṣibhiḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The gods dwell upon Meru along with sages."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 25,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूर्यः प्रदक्षिणं मेरुं भ्रमते कालचक्रवत्।",
    "transliteration": "sūryaḥ pradakṣiṇaṃ meruṃ bhramate kāla-cakra-vat ||",
    "translation_english": "The sun circles Mount Meru like the wheel of time."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 26,
    "sanskrit_text": "ततोऽहोरात्रमासाश्च ऋतवः संवत्सरास्तथा।",
    "transliteration": "tato’horātra-māsāś ca ṛtavaḥ saṃvatsarās tathā ||",
    "translation_english": "From this movement arise days, nights, months, seasons, and years."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 27,
    "sanskrit_text": "चन्द्रः पुष्णाति भूतानि सोमरूपेण संस्थितः।",
    "transliteration": "candraḥ puṣṇāti bhūtāni soma-rūpeṇa saṃsthitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The moon nourishes beings by assuming the form of Soma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 28,
    "sanskrit_text": "वायुरन्नं पचत्यत्र प्राणरूपेण संस्थितः।",
    "transliteration": "vāyur annaṃ pacaty atra prāṇa-rūpeṇa saṃsthitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Vāyu digests food by dwelling within beings as vital breath."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 29,
    "sanskrit_text": "अग्निर्देहेषु वैश्वानरः सर्वेषां धारणात्मकः।",
    "transliteration": "agnir deheṣu vaiśvānaraḥ sarveṣāṃ dhāraṇātmakaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Agni resides in all bodies as Vaiśvānara, sustaining life."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 30,
    "sanskrit_text": "जलमन्नं स्मृतं देवैः प्राणानां धारणं परम्।",
    "transliteration": "jalam annaṃ smṛtaṃ devaiḥ prāṇānāṃ dhāraṇaṃ param ||",
    "translation_english": "Water is considered food by the gods and the supreme support of life."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 31,
    "sanskrit_text": "पृथिवी सर्वभूतानां धारिणी पुण्यसंहिता।",
    "transliteration": "pṛthivī sarva-bhūtānāṃ dhāriṇī puṇya-saṃhitā ||",
    "translation_english": "The Earth supports all beings and is filled with sacred merit."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 32,
    "sanskrit_text": "एते पञ्च महाभूताः सृष्टिस्थितिलयात्मकाः।",
    "transliteration": "ete pañca mahābhūtāḥ sṛṣṭi-sthiti-layātmakāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "These five great elements govern creation, preservation, and dissolution."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 33,
    "sanskrit_text": "गुणत्रयसमायुक्तं जगदेतच्चराचरम्।",
    "transliteration": "guṇa-traya-samāyuktaṃ jagad etac carācaram ||",
    "translation_english": "This moving and unmoving world is composed of the three guṇas."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 34,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्त्वं रजस्तमश्चैव प्रवर्तन्ते यथाक्रमम्।",
    "transliteration": "sattvaṃ rajas tamaś caiva pravartante yathākramam ||",
    "translation_english": "Sattva, Rajas, and Tamas operate in due order."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 35,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्त्वात् ज्ञानं रजः कर्म तमसो मोह उच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "sattvāt jñānaṃ rajaḥ karma tamaso moha ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "From Sattva arises knowledge, from Rajas action, and from Tamas delusion."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 36,
    "sanskrit_text": "एतद् गुणमयं विश्वं ज्ञात्वा मुच्येत पण्डितः।",
    "transliteration": "etad guṇa-mayaṃ viśvaṃ jñātvā mucyeta paṇḍitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The wise are liberated by understanding this guṇa-based universe."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 37,
    "sanskrit_text": "अविद्यया समाविष्टा जीवाः संसारमाश्रिताः।",
    "transliteration": "avidyayā samāviṣṭā jīvāḥ saṃsāram āśritāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Beings enveloped by ignorance remain bound to worldly existence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 38,
    "sanskrit_text": "विद्यया तु विमुच्यन्ते विष्णुपदमवाप्नुयुः।",
    "transliteration": "vidyayā tu vimucyante viṣṇu-padam avāpnuyuḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Through true knowledge they are liberated and attain Viṣṇu’s abode."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 39,
    "sanskrit_text": "विष्णुः सर्वगतः शुद्धो जगतः कारणं परम्।",
    "transliteration": "viṣṇuḥ sarva-gataḥ śuddho jagataḥ kāraṇaṃ param ||",
    "translation_english": "Viṣṇu is all-pervading, pure, and the supreme cause of the universe."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 40,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं ब्रह्माण्डमाख्यातं मया ते मुनिसत्तमाः।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ brahmāṇḍam ākhyātaṃ mayā te muni-sattamāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the nature of the cosmic universe has been explained to you, O great sages."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 9,
    "verse": 41,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति ब्रह्मपुराणे नवमोऽध्यायः समाप्तः।",
    "transliteration": "iti brahma-purāṇe navamo’dhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the ninth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },


  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूत उवाच। मन्वन्तराणि वक्ष्यामि यथावत् क्रमशः शुभम्।",
    "transliteration": "sūta uvāca | manvantarāṇi vakṣyāmi yathāvat kramaśaḥ śubham ||",
    "translation_english": "Sūta said: I shall now describe the Manvantaras in proper and auspicious order."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "स्वायम्भुवो मनुः पूर्वं लोकान् धर्मे न्यवेशयत्।",
    "transliteration": "svāyambhuvo manuḥ pūrvaṃ lokān dharme nyaveśayat ||",
    "translation_english": "First was Svāyambhuva Manu, who established the worlds in righteousness."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "तस्य पुत्राः प्रजाः सर्वाः धर्ममार्गे प्रतिष्ठिताः।",
    "transliteration": "tasya putrāḥ prajāḥ sarvāḥ dharmamārge pratiṣṭhitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "His sons and all beings were firmly established on the path of dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "प्रियव्रतोत्तानपादौ तस्य वंशप्रवर्तकौ।",
    "transliteration": "priyavrato-uttānapādau tasya vaṃśa-pravartakau ||",
    "translation_english": "Priyavrata and Uttānapāda became the progenitors of his lineage."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "प्रियव्रतस्य पुत्रास्तु सप्त द्वीपान् विभक्तवान्।",
    "transliteration": "priyavratasya putrās tu sapta dvīpān vibhaktavān ||",
    "translation_english": "The sons of Priyavrata divided the earth into seven continents."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "उत्तानपादस्य ध्रुवः कीर्तिमान् लोकविश्रुतः।",
    "transliteration": "uttānapādasya dhruvaḥ kīrtimān loka-viśrutaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Dhruva, the son of Uttānapāda, became renowned and celebrated in all worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "ध्रुवलोकं समासाद्य स्थिरतां प्राप सः ध्रुवः।",
    "transliteration": "dhruvalokaṃ samāsādya sthiratāṃ prāpa saḥ dhruvaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Attaining Dhruva-loka, he achieved eternal stability."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "तस्य वंशे प्रजाः सर्वाः धर्मज्ञा लोकसंमताः।",
    "transliteration": "tasya vaṃśe prajāḥ sarvāḥ dharmajñā loka-sammatāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "All beings in his lineage were righteous and honored by the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 9,
    "sanskrit_text": "मनवो बहवो जाताः काले काले व्यवस्थिताः।",
    "transliteration": "manavo bahavo jātāḥ kāle kāle vyavasthitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Many Manus arose in different ages, each established in their time."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 10,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां धर्मप्रवृत्तिः स्यात् प्रजानां हितकारिणी।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ dharma-pravṛttiḥ syāt prajānāṃ hitakāriṇī ||",
    "translation_english": "Their governance of dharma ensured the welfare of all beings."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 11,
    "sanskrit_text": "मन्वन्तरेषु देवाश्च ऋषयश्च प्रतिष्ठिताः।",
    "transliteration": "manvantareṣu devāś ca ṛṣayaś ca pratiṣṭhitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "In each Manvantara, gods and sages were duly established."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 12,
    "sanskrit_text": "इन्द्रा मनुगुणा लोके नियुक्ताः कर्मसिद्धये।",
    "transliteration": "indrā manu-guṇā loke niyuktāḥ karma-siddhaye ||",
    "translation_english": "Indras, suited to each Manu, were appointed to govern the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "सप्तर्षयोऽपि धर्मज्ञा लोकपालनतत्पराः।",
    "transliteration": "saptarṣayo’pi dharmajñā loka-pālana-tatparāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The seven sages, knowers of dharma, were devoted to preserving the worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं मन्वन्तराण्युक्त्वा वंशान् वक्ष्याम्यतः परम्।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ manvantarāṇy uktvā vaṃśān vakṣyāmy ataḥ param ||",
    "translation_english": "Having thus described the Manvantaras, I shall now speak of the dynasties."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूर्यवंशोऽथ चन्द्रवंशो राज्ञां कीर्तिप्रदायकौ।",
    "transliteration": "sūryavaṃśo’tha candravaṃśo rājñāṃ kīrti-pradāyakau ||",
    "translation_english": "The Solar and Lunar dynasties bestowed great fame upon kings."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां वंशप्रसूतास्तु धर्मज्ञा लोकविश्रुताः।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ vaṃśa-prasūtās tu dharmajñā loka-viśrutāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Those born in these lineages were righteous and renowned in the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "राजर्षयश्च बहवो जगतः पालनं गताः।",
    "transliteration": "rājarṣayaś ca bahavo jagataḥ pālanaṃ gatāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Many royal sages arose, devoted to protecting the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण पृथिवीं पालयन्तः कीर्तिमवाप्नुयुः।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa pṛthivīṃ pālayantaḥ kīrtim avāpnuyuḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Ruling the earth through dharma, they attained lasting glory."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "एषा सृष्टिः पुरा प्रोक्ता ब्रह्मणा लोककारिणा।",
    "transliteration": "eṣā sṛṣṭiḥ purā proktā brahmaṇā loka-kāriṇā ||",
    "translation_english": "This creation was spoken of long ago by Brahmā, the creator of worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "अतः परं प्रवक्ष्यामि वंशानां विस्तरं शुभम्।",
    "transliteration": "ataḥ paraṃ pravakṣyāmi vaṃśānāṃ vistaraṃ śubham ||",
    "translation_english": "Hereafter, I shall describe the detailed and auspicious genealogies."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 21,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूर्यवंशस्य प्रथिताः शूरा राजर्षयः सदा।",
    "transliteration": "sūryavaṃśasya prathitāḥ śūrā rājarṣayaḥ sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "In the Solar dynasty, valiant royal sages were always renowned."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 22,
    "sanskrit_text": "महर्षयः सन्तु ते सर्वे धर्मे स्थितिसंपन्नाः।",
    "transliteration": "maharṣayaḥ santu te sarve dharme sthiti-sampannāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "All these great sages were firmly established in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 23,
    "sanskrit_text": "चन्द्रवंशस्य राजानः कीर्तिं लभन्ते विभुः।",
    "transliteration": "candravaṃśasya rājānaḥ kīrtiṃ labhante vibhuḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Kings of the Lunar dynasty attained great fame."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 24,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां पुत्राः प्रजाः च धर्मे प्रतिष्ठिताः सदा।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ putrāḥ prajāḥ ca dharme pratiṣṭhitāḥ sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "Their sons and all subjects were always established in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 25,
    "sanskrit_text": "मनुसुश्रीणां वंशे देवाः सप्तर्षयश्च वै।",
    "transliteration": "manuśrīṇāṃ vaṃśe devāḥ saptarṣayaś ca vai ||",
    "translation_english": "In the noble line of Manus, gods and the seven sages were present."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 26,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां धर्मे प्रवृत्ते लोकपालनं समुत्कृष्टम्।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ dharme pravṛtte lokapālanaṃ samutkṛṣṭam ||",
    "translation_english": "When they were active in dharma, world protection reached perfection."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 27,
    "sanskrit_text": "राजर्षयः प्रजाः च पृथिवीं पालयन्ति धर्मतः।",
    "transliteration": "rājarṣayaḥ prajāḥ ca pṛthivīṃ pālayanti dharmataḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Royal sages and kings govern the earth according to dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 28,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्वे राजानः शूरा धर्मसिद्धिं प्रयान्ति च।",
    "transliteration": "sarve rājānaḥ śūrā dharma-siddhiṃ prayānti ca ||",
    "translation_english": "All courageous kings advance toward perfection in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 29,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां वंशे बहवो प्रजाः लोकहिते प्रतिष्ठिताः।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ vaṃśe bahavo prajāḥ lokahite pratiṣṭhitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "In their lineage, many subjects were established for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 30,
    "sanskrit_text": "ते वंशाः पुरा वर्णिताः ब्रह्मणो देवतासु च।",
    "transliteration": "te vaṃśāḥ purā varṇitāḥ brahmaṇo devatāsu ca ||",
    "translation_english": "These dynasties were described long ago by Brahmā among the gods."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 31,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूर्यवंशो लभते कीर्तिं धर्मज्ञः लोकप्रियः।",
    "transliteration": "sūryavaṃśo labhate kīrtiṃ dharmajñaḥ loka-priyaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The Solar dynasty attains fame, being righteous and beloved of the people."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 32,
    "sanskrit_text": "चन्द्रवंशोऽपि बहुभिर्जनैः प्रतिष्ठितः सदा।",
    "transliteration": "candravaṃśo’pi bahubhir janaiḥ pratiṣṭhitaḥ sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "The Lunar dynasty too was always established by numerous people."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 33,
    "sanskrit_text": "राजर्षयः सन्तु सर्वे धर्मे स्थितिसंपन्नाः।",
    "transliteration": "rājarṣayaḥ santu sarve dharme sthiti-sampannāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "May all royal sages be firmly established in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 34,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां पुत्राः शूराः सन्तु कीर्तिसम्पन्नाः।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ putrāḥ śūrāḥ santu kīrti-sampannāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "May their sons be valiant and endowed with fame."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 35,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं वंशाः संप्राप्ताः धर्मज्ञा लोकहिते सदा।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ vaṃśāḥ saṃprāptāḥ dharmajñā lokahite sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the dynasties have always been established, righteous, and for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 36,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां वंशानुक्रमेण वर्णनं कुर्वेऽहं श्रोत्रे।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ vaṃśānukrameṇa varṇanaṃ kurve’haṃ śrotre ||",
    "translation_english": "I now describe the dynasties in sequence for those who listen."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 37,
    "sanskrit_text": "मन्वन्तराणि च वक्ष्यामि परं पितृभ्यः सदा।",
    "transliteration": "manvantarāṇi ca vakṣyāmi paraṃ pitṛbhyaḥ sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "I shall describe the Manvantaras and their supreme lineage for the forefathers."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 38,
    "sanskrit_text": "एते वंशाः पुरा प्रोक्ताः ब्रह्मणा लोककारिणा।",
    "transliteration": "ete vaṃśāḥ purā proktāḥ brahmaṇā loka-kāriṇā ||",
    "translation_english": "These dynasties were described long ago by Brahmā, the benefactor of worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 39,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्यं धर्मं च युक्त्वा लोकहिते प्रवर्तिताः।",
    "transliteration": "satyaṃ dharmaṃ ca yuktvā lokahite pravartitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Righteous and truthful, they acted always for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 10,
    "verse": 40,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं दशमोऽध्यायः समाप्तः ब्रह्मपुराणे सदा।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ daśamo’dhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ brahma-purāṇe sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the tenth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },

  
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूत उवाच। वक्ष्यामि राजर्षीनां वंशानुक्रमेण शुभम्।",
    "transliteration": "sūta uvāca | vakṣyāmi rājarṣīnāṃ vaṃśānukrameṇa śubham ||",
    "translation_english": "Sūta said: I shall now describe the genealogies of royal sages in proper order."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "मन्वन्तराणि संप्राप्तानि धर्ममार्गे स्थितानि च।",
    "transliteration": "manvantarāṇi saṃprāptāni dharmamārge sthitāni ca ||",
    "translation_english": "The Manvantaras had arrived, and all were firmly established in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां राजर्षयः सन्तु लोकहिते प्रवर्तिताः।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ rājarṣayaḥ santu lokahite pravartitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Their royal sages acted for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूर्यवंशस्य राजानः धर्मसिद्धिं प्राप्नुवन्ति।",
    "transliteration": "sūryavaṃśasya rājānaḥ dharma-siddhiṃ prāpnuvanti ||",
    "translation_english": "Kings of the Solar dynasty attained perfection in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "चन्द्रवंशस्य राजानः प्रजा-हिते प्रतिष्ठिताः।",
    "transliteration": "candravaṃśasya rājānaḥ prajā-hite pratiṣṭhitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Kings of the Lunar dynasty were established for the welfare of their subjects."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "मनुश्रीणां वंशे देवाश्च सप्तर्षयश्च सन्तु।",
    "transliteration": "manuśrīṇāṃ vaṃśe devāś ca saptarṣayaś ca santu ||",
    "translation_english": "In the lineage of noble Manus, gods and the seven sages were present."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 11,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां धर्मे प्रवृत्ते लोकपालनं समुत्कृष्टम्।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ dharme pravṛtte lokapālanaṃ samutkṛṣṭam ||",
    "translation_english": "When they acted according to dharma, world protection reached perfection."
  },
