  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 25,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां धर्मे प्रवृत्ते लोकपालनं समुत्कृष्टम्।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ dharme pravṛtte lokapālanaṃ samutkṛṣṭam ||",
    "translation_english": "When they acted in dharma, world protection reached excellence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 26,
    "sanskrit_text": "राजर्षयश्च सन्तु धर्मे स्थितिसंपन्नाः।",
    "transliteration": "rājarṣayaś ca santu dharme sthiti-sampannāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "May all royal sages be firmly established in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 27,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां पुत्राः शूराः सन्तु कीर्तिसम्पन्नाः।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ putrāḥ śūrāḥ santu kīrti-sampannāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "May their sons be valiant and endowed with fame."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 28,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्वे राजर्षयः धर्मे स्थिराः लोकहिते च।",
    "transliteration": "sarve rājarṣayaḥ dharme sthirāḥ lokahite ca ||",
    "translation_english": "All royal sages remain steadfast in dharma for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 29,
    "sanskrit_text": "सूर्यवंशस्य राजानः प्रजा-हिते प्रवर्तिताः।",
    "transliteration": "sūryavaṃśasya rājānaḥ prajā-hite pravartitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Kings of the Solar dynasty acted continuously for the welfare of their subjects."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 30,
    "sanskrit_text": "चन्द्रवंशस्य राजानः धर्मसिद्धिं प्राप्नुवन्ति।",
    "transliteration": "candravaṃśasya rājānaḥ dharma-siddhiṃ prāpnuvanti ||",
    "translation_english": "Kings of the Lunar dynasty attained perfection in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 31,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां पुत्राः प्रजाः च धर्मे प्रतिष्ठिताः सदा।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ putrāḥ prajāḥ ca dharme pratiṣṭhitāḥ sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "Their sons and subjects were always established in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 32,
    "sanskrit_text": "मनुश्रीणां वंशे देवाश्च सप्तर्षयश्च वै।",
    "transliteration": "manuśrīṇāṃ vaṃśe devāś ca saptarṣayaś ca vai ||",
    "translation_english": "In the line of noble Manus, gods and the seven sages were present."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 33,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां धर्मे प्रवृत्ते लोकपालनं समुत्कृष्टम्।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ dharme pravṛtte lokapālanaṃ samutkṛṣṭam ||",
    "translation_english": "When they acted in dharma, world protection reached perfection."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 34,
    "sanskrit_text": "राजर्षयश्च सन्तु धर्मे स्थितिसंपन्नाः।",
    "transliteration": "rājarṣayaś ca santu dharme sthiti-sampannāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "May all royal sages be firmly established in dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 35,
    "sanskrit_text": "तेषां पुत्राः शूराः सन्तु कीर्तिसम्पन्नाः।",
    "transliteration": "teṣāṃ putrāḥ śūrāḥ santu kīrti-sampannāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "May their sons be valiant and renowned."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 36,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्वे राजर्षयः धर्मे स्थिराः लोकहिते च।",
    "transliteration": "sarve rājarṣayaḥ dharme sthirāḥ lokahite ca ||",
    "translation_english": "All royal sages remain steadfast in dharma for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 37,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं वंशाः पुरा वर्णिताः धर्मज्ञा लोकहिते सदा।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ vaṃśāḥ purā varṇitāḥ dharmajñā lokahite sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the dynasties were described long ago, righteous and for the welfare of the world."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 38,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं द्वादशोऽध्यायः समाप्तः ब्रह्मपुराणे सदा।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ dvādaśo’dhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ brahma-purāṇe sadā ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the twelfth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 39,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति द्वादशोऽध्यायः संपूर्णः भक्तिपूर्वकं पठितः।",
    "transliteration": "iti dvādaśo’dhyāyaḥ saṃpūrṇaḥ bhakti-pūrvakaṃ paṭhitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the twelfth chapter has been completed, read with devotion."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 12,
    "verse": 40,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्वे पाठकाः पुण्यं लभन्तु धर्मसिद्धये।",
    "transliteration": "sarve pāṭhakāḥ puṇyaṃ labhantu dharma-siddhaye ||",
    "translation_english": "May all readers attain merit and perfection in dharma."
  },

  
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "अथ त्रयोदशोऽध्यायः ब्रह्मपुराणे प्रवर्तते।",
    "transliteration": "atha trayodaśo’dhyāyaḥ brahma-purāṇe pravartate ||",
    "translation_english": "Now begins the thirteenth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "कालस्य स्वरूपं विप्राणां ब्रह्मा सम्यगुवाच ह।",
    "transliteration": "kālasya svarūpaṃ viprāṇāṃ brahmā samyag uvāca ha ||",
    "translation_english": "Brahmā clearly explained to the sages the true nature of Time."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "कालः सृजति भूतानि काल एव विनाशकृत्।",
    "transliteration": "kālaḥ sṛjati bhūtāni kāla eva vināśakṛt ||",
    "translation_english": "Time creates all beings, and Time itself causes their destruction."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "कालातीतं परं ब्रह्म न कालेन विनश्यति।",
    "transliteration": "kālātītaṃ paraṃ brahma na kālena vinaśyati ||",
    "translation_english": "The Supreme Brahman transcends time and is never destroyed by it."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "युगानि च चतुर्विप्राः कीर्तयामास स प्रभुः।",
    "transliteration": "yugāni ca catur viprāḥ kīrtayāmāsa sa prabhuḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "The Lord then described the four Yugas to the sages."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "कृतं त्रेता द्वापरं च कलिश्च क्रमशः स्मृताः।",
    "transliteration": "kṛtaṃ tretā dvāparaṃ ca kaliś ca kramaśaḥ smṛtāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Kṛta, Tretā, Dvāpara, and Kali are remembered in that order."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मः पादचतुष्कोऽत्र कृतयुगे प्रतिष्ठितः।",
    "transliteration": "dharmaḥ pāda-catuṣko’tra kṛta-yuge pratiṣṭhitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "In the Kṛta Yuga, dharma stands firmly on all four legs."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "त्रेतायां पादहीनः स्याद् द्वापरे द्वौ विनश्यतः।",
    "transliteration": "tretāyāṃ pāda-hīnaḥ syād dvāpare dvau vinaśyataḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "In Tretā one leg is lost, and in Dvāpara two legs decline."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 9,
    "sanskrit_text": "कलौ तु पादमात्रेण धर्मः तिष्ठति दुर्बलः।",
    "transliteration": "kalau tu pāda-mātreṇa dharmaḥ tiṣṭhati durbalaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "In Kali Yuga, dharma survives weakly on only one leg."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 10,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्यं दया तपो दानं युगे युगे विनश्यति।",
    "transliteration": "satyaṃ dayā tapo dānaṃ yuge yuge vinaśyati ||",
    "translation_english": "Truth, compassion, austerity, and charity decline with each Yuga."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 11,
    "sanskrit_text": "कलेर्दोषनिधे राजन् धर्मो नामैक एव हि।",
    "transliteration": "kaler doṣa-nidhe rājan dharmo nāmaika eva hi ||",
    "translation_english": "O King, Kali is an ocean of faults, yet one form of dharma remains."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 12,
    "sanskrit_text": "हरिनामस्मृतिं पुण्यां मोक्षसाधनमुत्तमम्।",
    "transliteration": "hari-nāma-smṛtiṃ puṇyāṃ mokṣa-sādhanam uttamam ||",
    "translation_english": "Remembrance of Hari’s name is the supreme means of liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "यज्ञाः कृतयुगे प्रोक्ता त्रेतायां तप उच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "yajñāḥ kṛta-yuge proktā tretāyāṃ tapa ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Sacrifice dominates Kṛta Yuga, while austerity prevails in Tretā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "द्वापरे परिचर्या स्यात् कलौ दानं विशिष्यते।",
    "transliteration": "dvāpare paricaryā syāt kalau dānaṃ viśiṣyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Service defines Dvāpara Yuga, while charity excels in Kali."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं युगधर्माः प्रोक्ताः ब्रह्मणा लोकहेतवे।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ yuga-dharmāḥ proktāḥ brahmaṇā loka-hetave ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the duties of the Yugas were declared by Brahmā for the world's welfare."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "मन्वन्तराणां क्रमश्च संक्षेपेण निगद्यते।",
    "transliteration": "manvantarāṇāṃ kramaś ca saṃkṣepeṇa nigadyate ||",
    "translation_english": "The sequence of Manvantaras is then briefly described."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "चतुर्दश मनवः प्रोक्ता ब्रह्मणः कल्पसम्भवाः।",
    "transliteration": "caturdaśa manavaḥ proktā brahmaṇaḥ kalpa-sambhavāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Fourteen Manus arise in each Kalpa of Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "इन्द्राः सप्तर्षयश्चैव प्रत्येकं मन्वन्तरे।",
    "transliteration": "indrāḥ saptarṣayaś caiva pratyekaṃ manvantare ||",
    "translation_english": "Each Manvantara has its own Indra and seven sages."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं कालविभागोऽयं ब्रह्मणा परिकीर्तितः।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ kāla-vibhāgo’yaṃ brahmaṇā parikīrtitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the divisions of time were expounded by Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "एतद्विज्ञाय धर्मात्मा मुच्यते नात्र संशयः।",
    "transliteration": "etad vijñāya dharmātmā mucyate nātra saṃśayaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "One who understands this with righteousness is liberated—without doubt."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 21,
    "sanskrit_text": "कालो हि सर्वभूतानां प्रभवो नाश एव च।",
    "transliteration": "kālo hi sarva-bhūtānāṃ prabhavo nāśa eva ca ||",
    "translation_english": "Time alone is the source and the destroyer of all beings."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 22,
    "sanskrit_text": "न कश्चित्कालमतिक्रम्य जीवितुं शक्नोति हि।",
    "transliteration": "na kaścit kālam atikramya jīvituṃ śaknoti hi ||",
    "translation_english": "No one can live by surpassing the power of Time."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 23,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्गे स्थितौ लये चैव कालः कारणमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "sarge sthitau laye caiva kālaḥ kāraṇam ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "In creation, preservation, and dissolution, Time is declared the cause."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 24,
    "sanskrit_text": "ब्रह्मा विष्णुश्च रुद्रश्च कालस्य वशवर्तिनः।",
    "transliteration": "brahmā viṣṇuś ca rudraś ca kālasya vaśa-vartinaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Brahmā, Viṣṇu, and Rudra act under the governance of Time."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 25,
    "sanskrit_text": "कालात्परतरं ब्रह्म नित्यं शाश्वतमव्ययम्।",
    "transliteration": "kālāt parataraṃ brahma nityaṃ śāśvatam avyayam ||",
    "translation_english": "Beyond Time exists the eternal, imperishable Supreme Brahman."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 26,
    "sanskrit_text": "तद्ब्रह्म ज्ञायते योगैः शुद्धचित्तैर्महात्मभिः।",
    "transliteration": "tad brahma jñāyate yogaiḥ śuddha-cittair mahātmabhiḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "That Brahman is realized through yoga by pure-minded great souls."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 27,
    "sanskrit_text": "कालबद्धः स जीवात्मा कर्मपाशेन बध्यते।",
    "transliteration": "kāla-baddhaḥ sa jīvātmā karma-pāśena badhyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Bound by Time, the individual soul is tied by the bonds of karma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 28,
    "sanskrit_text": "ज्ञानदीपेन तं पाशं छित्त्वा मुक्तो भवेत् नरः।",
    "transliteration": "jñāna-dīpena taṃ pāśaṃ chittvā mukto bhavet naraḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "By the lamp of knowledge, one cuts these bonds and becomes liberated."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 29,
    "sanskrit_text": "न कर्मणा न संतानेन न धनेन विमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "na karmaṇā na saṃtānena na dhanena vimucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Neither action, progeny, nor wealth can grant liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 30,
    "sanskrit_text": "ज्ञानेनैव तु कैवल्यं प्राप्यते नात्र संशयः।",
    "transliteration": "jñānenaiva tu kaivalyaṃ prāpyate nātra saṃśayaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Liberation is attained only through knowledge—there is no doubt."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 31,
    "sanskrit_text": "ज्ञानं च भक्तिसंयुक्तं मोक्षमार्गं प्रपद्यते।",
    "transliteration": "jñānaṃ ca bhakti-saṃyuktaṃ mokṣa-mārgaṃ prapadyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Knowledge united with devotion leads one to the path of liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 32,
    "sanskrit_text": "विष्णुभक्त्या विशेषेण कालबन्धो विनश्यति।",
    "transliteration": "viṣṇu-bhaktyā viśeṣeṇa kāla-bandho vinaśyati ||",
    "translation_english": "Through devotion to Viṣṇu, the bondage of Time is destroyed."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 33,
    "sanskrit_text": "यः स्मरेत् पुण्डरीकाक्षं स याति परमां गतिम्।",
    "transliteration": "yaḥ smaret puṇḍarīkākṣaṃ sa yāti paramāṃ gatim ||",
    "translation_english": "One who remembers the Lotus-eyed Lord attains the supreme state."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 34,
    "sanskrit_text": "न पुनर्जन्म संसारे तस्य विद्यते कचित्।",
    "transliteration": "na punar-janma saṃsāre tasya vidyate kvacit ||",
    "translation_english": "For such a soul, rebirth in this world no longer exists."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 35,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं धर्मं समाख्यातं कालतत्त्वसमन्वितम्।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ dharmaṃ samākhyātaṃ kāla-tattva-samanvitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus dharma has been explained together with the principle of Time."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 36,
    "sanskrit_text": "श्रुत्वैतत् पुण्यमाख्यानं मुच्यते पापकर्मभिः।",
    "transliteration": "śrutvaitat puṇyam ākhyānaṃ mucyate pāpa-karmabhiḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Hearing this sacred account frees one from sinful actions."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 37,
    "sanskrit_text": "यः पठेन्नियतं भक्त्या स याति ब्रह्मणः पदम्।",
    "transliteration": "yaḥ paṭhen niyataṃ bhaktyā sa yāti brahmaṇaḥ padam ||",
    "translation_english": "One who regularly recites this with devotion reaches the abode of Brahman."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 38,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति कालस्य माहात्म्यं ब्रह्मणा समुदाहृतम्।",
    "transliteration": "iti kālasya māhātmyaṃ brahmaṇā samudāhṛtam ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the greatness of Time was proclaimed by Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 39,
    "sanskrit_text": "लोकानां हितकामेन मुनिभ्यः कथितं पुरा।",
    "transliteration": "lokānāṃ hita-kāmena munibhyaḥ kathitaṃ purā ||",
    "translation_english": "This was narrated long ago to the sages for the welfare of the worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 13,
    "verse": 40,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं त्रयोदशोऽध्यायः समाप्तः ब्रह्मपुराणे।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ trayodaśo’dhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ brahma-purāṇe ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the thirteenth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },


  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "ब्रह्मोवाच। शृणु वक्ष्यामि धर्मज्ञानसमन्वितम्।",
    "transliteration": "brahmovāca | śṛṇu vakṣyāmi dharma-jñāna-samanvitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Brahmā said: Listen as I explain the principles of dharma combined with true knowledge."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "येन विज्ञानमात्रेण संसारात् परिमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "yena vijñāna-mātreṇa saṃsārāt parimucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "By which realization alone one is freed from worldly existence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मः मूलं जगत्सर्वं धर्मे लोकाः प्रतिष्ठिताः।",
    "transliteration": "dharmaḥ mūlaṃ jagat sarvaṃ dharme lokāḥ pratiṣṭhitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Dharma is the foundation of the entire universe; all worlds rest upon dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण ध्रियते लोकः धर्मेणैव प्रसीदति।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa dhriyate lokaḥ dharmeṇaiva prasīdati ||",
    "translation_english": "By dharma the world is sustained, and through dharma it prospers."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्महीनः क्षयं याति पुरुषो नात्र संशयः।",
    "transliteration": "dharma-hīnaḥ kṣayaṃ yāti puruṣo nātra saṃśayaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "A person devoid of dharma meets destruction—there is no doubt."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "सत्यं दानं तपः शौचं धर्मस्यैतानि लक्षणम्।",
    "transliteration": "satyaṃ dānaṃ tapaḥ śaucaṃ dharmasyaitāni lakṣaṇam ||",
    "translation_english": "Truth, charity, austerity, and purity are the marks of dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "एतेन मार्गेण नरो विष्णुलोकं स गच्छति।",
    "transliteration": "etena mārgeṇa naro viṣṇu-lokaṃ sa gacchati ||",
    "translation_english": "By following this path, a person attains the realm of Viṣṇu."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "भक्त्या समन्वितं ज्ञानं मोक्षसाधनमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "bhaktyā samanvitaṃ jñānaṃ mokṣa-sādhanam ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Knowledge united with devotion is said to be the means to liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 9,
    "sanskrit_text": "न ज्ञानं भक्तिहीनस्य न भक्तिर्ज्ञानवर्जिता।",
    "transliteration": "na jñānaṃ bhakti-hīnasya na bhaktir jñāna-varjitā ||",
    "translation_english": "Knowledge without devotion is fruitless, and devotion without knowledge is incomplete."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 10,
    "sanskrit_text": "उभाभ्यां जायते मुक्तिर्नान्यथा विद्यते क्वचित्।",
    "transliteration": "ubhābhyāṃ jāyate muktir nānyathā vidyate kvacit ||",
    "translation_english": "Liberation arises from both together; it is not attained otherwise."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 11,
    "sanskrit_text": "विष्णुं सर्वेषु भूतेषु पश्यन्नात्मानमाप्नुयात्।",
    "transliteration": "viṣṇuṃ sarveṣu bhūteṣu paśyann ātmānam āpnuyāt ||",
    "translation_english": "Seeing Viṣṇu in all beings, one realizes the Self."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 12,
    "sanskrit_text": "समदर्शी सदा योगी द्वेषरागविवर्जितः।",
    "transliteration": "sama-darśī sadā yogī dveṣa-rāga-vivarjitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Such a yogi sees all equally, free from hatred and attachment."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 13,
    "sanskrit_text": "स एव मुक्त इत्युक्तः शास्त्रदृष्ट्या सुनिश्चितः।",
    "transliteration": "sa eva mukta ity uktaḥ śāstra-dṛṣṭyā niścitāḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "According to the scriptures, such a person alone is called liberated."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 14,
    "sanskrit_text": "न गृहस्थो न संन्यासी केवलं धर्मवान् भवेत्।",
    "transliteration": "na gṛhastho na saṃnyāsī kevalaṃ dharmavān bhavet ||",
    "translation_english": "Neither householder nor renunciate matters—only righteousness does."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 15,
    "sanskrit_text": "आचारेणैव शुद्धिः स्यात् न वेशेन न जातिभिः।",
    "transliteration": "ācāreṇaiva śuddhiḥ syāt na veśena na jātibhiḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Purity arises from conduct alone, not from attire or birth."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 16,
    "sanskrit_text": "यः सर्वभूतहिते रतः स वै ब्राह्मण उच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "yaḥ sarva-bhūta-hite rataḥ sa vai brāhmaṇa ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "One devoted to the welfare of all beings is truly called a Brāhmaṇa."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 17,
    "sanskrit_text": "एतद् धर्मस्य सारं तु कथितं ते महामुने।",
    "transliteration": "etad dharmasya sāraṃ tu kathitaṃ te mahāmune ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus the essence of dharma has been explained to you, O great sage."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 18,
    "sanskrit_text": "श्रुत्वैतद् धर्ममाख्यानं नरः पापैः प्रमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "śrutvaitad dharmam ākhyānaṃ naraḥ pāpaiḥ pramucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Hearing this discourse on dharma frees a person from sins."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 19,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मे स्थितो नरः सम्यग् विष्णोः पदमवाप्नुयात्।",
    "transliteration": "dharme sthito naraḥ samyag viṣṇoḥ padam avāpnuyāt ||",
    "translation_english": "Established firmly in dharma, one attains the abode of Viṣṇu."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 20,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति धर्मप्रकरणं प्रारब्धं ब्रह्मणा पुरा।",
    "transliteration": "iti dharma-prakaraṇaṃ prārabdhaṃ brahmaṇā purā ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus begins the discourse on dharma as expounded long ago by Brahmā."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 21,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मेण हीनः पुरुषः पशुतुल्योऽभिजायते।",
    "transliteration": "dharmeṇa hīnaḥ puruṣaḥ paśu-tulyo’bhijāyate ||",
    "translation_english": "A person devoid of dharma becomes equal to a beast."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 22,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मयुक्तो मनुष्यस्तु देवतुल्यः प्रकीर्तितः।",
    "transliteration": "dharma-yukto manuṣyas tu deva-tulyaḥ prakīrtitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "A human endowed with dharma is proclaimed equal to the gods."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 23,
    "sanskrit_text": "न धर्मात् परमो लाभो न सुखं धर्मतः परम्।",
    "transliteration": "na dharmāt paramo lābho na sukhaṃ dharmataḥ param ||",
    "translation_english": "There is no gain higher than dharma, and no happiness greater than dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 24,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्म एव हतो हन्ति धर्मो रक्षति रक्षितः।",
    "transliteration": "dharma eva hato hanti dharmo rakṣati rakṣitaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Dharma, when destroyed, destroys; when protected, it protects."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 25,
    "sanskrit_text": "तस्माद्धर्मो न हन्तव्यो मा नो धर्मो हतोऽवधीत्।",
    "transliteration": "tasmād dharmo na hantavyo mā no dharmo hato’vadhīt ||",
    "translation_english": "Therefore dharma should never be destroyed, lest destroyed dharma destroy us."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 26,
    "sanskrit_text": "धर्मो विष्णुः स्मृतो लोके विष्णुर्धर्मः सनातनः।",
    "transliteration": "dharmo viṣṇuḥ smṛto loke viṣṇur dharmaḥ sanātanaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Dharma is remembered as Viṣṇu in this world, and Viṣṇu is eternal dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 27,
    "sanskrit_text": "यः पश्यति हरिं सर्वत्र स पश्यति न संशयः।",
    "transliteration": "yaḥ paśyati hariṃ sarvatra sa paśyati na saṃśayaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "One who sees Hari everywhere truly sees—there is no doubt."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 28,
    "sanskrit_text": "सर्वभूतेषु चात्मानं पश्यन्नात्मवित् उच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "sarva-bhūteṣu cātmānaṃ paśyann ātmavit ucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Seeing the Self in all beings, one is called a knower of the Self."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 29,
    "sanskrit_text": "एवं ज्ञानं समासेन धर्मयुक्तं प्रकीर्तितम्।",
    "transliteration": "evaṃ jñānaṃ samāsena dharma-yuktaṃ prakīrtitam ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus knowledge combined with dharma has been concisely proclaimed."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 30,
    "sanskrit_text": "ज्ञानं भक्त्या विना शुष्कं भक्तिर्ज्ञानविवर्जिता।",
    "transliteration": "jñānaṃ bhaktyā vinā śuṣkaṃ bhaktir jñāna-vivarjitā ||",
    "translation_english": "Knowledge without devotion is dry; devotion without knowledge is incomplete."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 31,
    "sanskrit_text": "उभयोर्योगतः सिद्धिर्मोक्षमार्गे प्रतिष्ठिता।",
    "transliteration": "ubhayor yogataḥ siddhir mokṣa-mārge pratiṣṭhitā ||",
    "translation_english": "Perfection arises from the union of both, firmly established on the path of liberation."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 32,
    "sanskrit_text": "विष्णुभक्त्या विशुद्धात्मा संसारं तरति ध्रुवम्।",
    "transliteration": "viṣṇu-bhaktyā viśuddhātmā saṃsāraṃ tarati dhruvam ||",
    "translation_english": "Through devotion to Viṣṇu, the purified soul surely crosses worldly existence."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 33,
    "sanskrit_text": "न तस्य पुनरावृत्तिः कर्मबन्धवशात् भवेत्।",
    "transliteration": "na tasya punarāvṛttiḥ karma-bandha-vaśāt bhavet ||",
    "translation_english": "For such a one, rebirth due to karmic bondage does not occur again."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 34,
    "sanskrit_text": "एष धर्मः समाख्यातो ब्रह्मणा लोककारणात्।",
    "transliteration": "eṣa dharmaḥ samākhyāto brahmaṇā loka-kāraṇāt ||",
    "translation_english": "This dharma was thus declared by Brahmā for the welfare of the worlds."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 35,
    "sanskrit_text": "श्रुत्वैतत् पुण्यमाख्यानं सर्वपापैः प्रमुच्यते।",
    "transliteration": "śrutvaitat puṇyam ākhyānaṃ sarva-pāpaiḥ pramucyate ||",
    "translation_english": "Hearing this sacred teaching, one is freed from all sins."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 36,
    "sanskrit_text": "पठन् वा श्रावयन् वापि धर्मलोकं स गच्छति।",
    "transliteration": "paṭhan vā śrāvayan vāpi dharma-lokaṃ sa gacchati ||",
    "translation_english": "Whether reciting or causing it to be heard, one attains the realm of dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 37,
    "sanskrit_text": "एतद् गुह्यतमं शास्त्रं न वक्तव्यं अभक्तये।",
    "transliteration": "etad guhyatamaṃ śāstraṃ na vaktavyaṃ abhaktaye ||",
    "translation_english": "This most secret teaching should not be spoken to the faithless."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 38,
    "sanskrit_text": "भक्ताय विनीताय श्रद्धालवे च कथ्यते।",
    "transliteration": "bhaktāya vinītāya śraddhālave ca kathyate ||",
    "translation_english": "It should be taught only to the devoted, humble, and faithful."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 39,
    "sanskrit_text": "इत्युक्त्वा ब्रह्मणा प्रोक्तं धर्मज्ञानमनुत्तमम्।",
    "transliteration": "ity uktvā brahmaṇā proktaṃ dharma-jñānam anuttamam ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus Brahmā concluded this supreme teaching of dharma and knowledge."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 14,
    "verse": 40,
    "sanskrit_text": "इति ब्रह्मपुराणे चतुर्दशोऽध्यायः समाप्तः।",
    "transliteration": "iti brahma-purāṇe caturdaśo’dhyāyaḥ samāptaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Thus ends the fourteenth chapter of the Brahma Purāṇa."
  },


  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 1,
    "sanskrit_text": "ब्रह्मोवाच। पुनरेव प्रवक्ष्यामि धर्मस्य परमं पदम्।",
    "transliteration": "brahmovāca | punar eva pravakṣyāmi dharmasya paramaṃ padam ||",
    "translation_english": "Brahmā said: Once again I shall explain the supreme state attained through dharma."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 2,
    "sanskrit_text": "यत् प्राप्य न निवर्तन्ते संसारदुःखसागरात्।",
    "transliteration": "yat prāpya na nivartante saṃsāra-duḥkha-sāgarāt ||",
    "translation_english": "Having attained it, beings do not return to the ocean of worldly suffering."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 3,
    "sanskrit_text": "अहिंसा सत्यवचनं दया शौचं क्षमा दमः।",
    "transliteration": "ahiṃsā satya-vacanaṃ dayā śaucaṃ kṣamā damaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Non-violence, truthfulness, compassion, purity, forgiveness, and self-restraint—"
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 4,
    "sanskrit_text": "एतैर्धर्मपथैः सम्यक् विष्णुलोकं स गच्छति।",
    "transliteration": "etair dharma-pathaiḥ samyak viṣṇu-lokaṃ sa gacchati ||",
    "translation_english": "By these righteous paths, one surely attains the realm of Viṣṇu."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 5,
    "sanskrit_text": "न तपांसि न दानानि न वेदाध्ययनं तथा।",
    "transliteration": "na tapāṃsi na dānāni na vedādhyayanaṃ tathā ||",
    "translation_english": "Neither austerities, nor charity, nor even Vedic study alone—"
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 6,
    "sanskrit_text": "भक्तिहीनस्य पुरुषस्य मोक्षहेतवः।",
    "transliteration": "bhakti-hīnasya puruṣasya mokṣa-hetavaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "—can become causes of liberation for a person devoid of devotion."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 7,
    "sanskrit_text": "भक्त्या तु केवया विष्णुः प्रसन्नः स्यात् न संशयः।",
    "transliteration": "bhaktyā tu kevalayā viṣṇuḥ prasannaḥ syāt na saṃśayaḥ ||",
    "translation_english": "Through pure devotion alone, Viṣṇu becomes pleased—there is no doubt."
  },
  {
    "purana_number": 7,
    "chapter": 15,
    "verse": 8,
    "sanskrit_text": "प्रसन्ने भगवत्येव मुक्तिः करस्थिता नृणाम्।",
    "transliteration": "prasanne bhagavaty eva muktiḥ kara-sthitā nṛṇām ||",
    "translation_english": "When the Lord is pleased, liberation rests in the hands of humans."
  },
  {
